==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Asterisk
<hw>As"ter*isk</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>asteriscus</ets>, Gr. <?/, dim. of <grk>'asth`r</grk> star. See
<er>Aster</er>.]</ety> <def>The figure of a star, thus, <?/, used in
printing and writing as a reference to a passage or note in the margin,
to supply the omission of letters or words, or to mark a word or phrase
as having a special character.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Asterism</ent>⟦br⟧
